column1: 56th Holly-Duane Raffin Festival of Races Mens 5000 Meters D1 Boys
The Skyline men's cross country team finished 12th with a total score of 309. Leading the team was Nicholas Yuan
column3: followed closely by Jack Robichaud (17:43.1) and Enshu Kuan (17:44.4). Bruno Cifaldi (17:57.2) and Kyle Krasan (18:01.8) rounded out the top five
column4: showcasing consistent performances across the board. The team demonstrated strong efforts in a competitive field
column5: keeping a tight spread among the top runners and building momentum for the rest of the season.
